            "config": {
              "id": "QUE59003",
              "question": "Which of the following is the best example of meeting our social goals through impression management?\n\u003cbr /\u003e",
              "order": "randomized",
              "presenterType": "RadioGroup",
              "presenterConfig": {
                "numberFormat": "none"
              },
              "choices": [
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "Two friends celebrate a birthday together for the first time in ten years."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "An animal lover volunteers at the local animal shelter on weekends."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "A rowdy college student presents herself as calm and polite so that her new roommate will like her."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "A new employee spends the day in his cubicle in order to avoid showing his weaknesses."
                }
              ]
            },
            "answerKey": {
              "assessmentType": "multiplechoice",
              "answers": {
                "answer_3": {
                  "score": 1.0,
                  "response": "That’s correct!"
                },
                "answer_2": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: Following your interests is not an attempt to manage people’s impressions of you. LO 4.3 Discuss what symbolic interactionists study and explain dramaturgy, ethnomethodology, and the social construction of reality."
                },
                "answer_1": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: While it is possible they will use impression management while celebrating together, the example does not demonstrate the concept. LO 4.3 Discuss what symbolic interactionists study and explain dramaturgy, ethnomethodology, and the social construction of reality."
                },
                "answer_4": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "sider this: We use impression management in the front stages of our lives. A personal work cubicle could be a back stage for some people. LO 4.3 Discuss what symbolic interactionists study and explain dramaturgy, ethnomethodology, and the social construction of reality."
                }
              }
            },
